SIMPLE: squatter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squatter
<hw>Squat"ter</hw> <pr>(-t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who squats;</def> <specif>specifically,</specif> <def>one who
settles unlawfully upon land without a title. In the United States and
Australia the term is sometimes applied also to a person who settles
lawfully upon government land under legal permission and restrictions,
before acquiring title.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In such a tract, <qex>squatters</qex> and trespassers were
tolerated to an extent now unknown.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>See <cref>Squat snipe</cref>,
under <er>Squat</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Squatter sovereignty</b></col>, <cd>the right claimed by
the squatters, or actual residents, of a Territory of the United States
to make their own laws.</cd> <mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark>
<au>Bartlett.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squatty</ent>⟦br⟧
